Actress Kemi Lala Akindoju has revealed how she appreciates any work of art, song, or film. In a recent tweet, the actress disclosed that good films, plays, songs, or albums leave her tearing up.   King Sunny Ade, NCC DG reward blind singer, Chude Mountain     Eedris Abdulkareem takes a swipe at Charly Boy after 19…     Lagos state announces plans to immortalise Sound Sultan   “When I really appreciate a work of art, a film, a script, a book, a performance, a play, an album, a song, a poem, a musical- I tear up,” she tweeted. Continuing, she said: “Actually, I cry. Storytelling in these forms is so beautiful.”